  "text": "The resulting algorithm for constructing the high-dimensional embedding is given in Fig. 4 . The graph-theoretical distances are computed using breadth-first-search (BFS) [CITATION_1] . We have previously shown that the HDE is a kind of m-dimensional layout of the graph and that PCA projections of the high-dimensional embedding typically yield nice layouts; see [CITATION_2] . Projections are just a type of linear combinations, so restricting the layout to lie inside span(X 1 , . . . , X m ) is plausible. In practice, we have found that choosing m ∼ 50 serves very well for producing a nice layout.",
